# AI Model Configuration Rules

## CRITICAL: Correct Model Strings (November 2025)

When working with AI APIs in this codebase, you MUST use these exact model strings:

### Gemini (Google)
- **CORRECT**: `gemini-3-pro-preview`
- **ALSO VALID**: `gemini-3-pro-latest`, `gemini-3-pro-preview-11-2025`
- **WRONG (404 error)**: `gemini-3-pro`, `gemini-3.0-pro`, `gemini-3.0-pro-latest`
- **WRONG (old model)**: `gemini-1.5-pro-latest`, `gemini-1.5-pro`, `gemini-2.0-flash`

### Claude (Anthropic)
- **CORRECT**: `claude-opus-4-5-20251101`
- **WRONG**: `claude-4.5-opus`, `claude-opus-4.5`, `claude-4-opus`

### GPT (OpenAI)
- **CORRECT**: `gpt-5.1`
- **WRONG**: `gpt-5.1-turbo`, `gpt-4o`, `gpt-4-turbo`

## MANDATORY BEHAVIOR

### If a model API returns 404 or "model not found":

1. **NEVER downgrade to an older model** (e.g., don't change gemini-3 to gemini-1.5)
2. **ALWAYS search online** for the correct model string
3. **Check official documentation**:
   - Gemini: https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/models
   - Claude: https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/models-overview
   - OpenAI: https://platform.openai.com/docs/models